## 2. CREATING AN IChatClient FROM OPENAI

### Namespace
`Microsoft.Extensions.AI`

### Creating from OpenAI
Use the OpenAI SDK and wrapper:

```csharp
using Microsoft.Extensions.AI;
using OpenAI.Chat;

// Step 1: Create OpenAI ChatClient
var openAIClient = new OpenAI.Chat.ChatClient(
    model: "gpt-4o-mini",
    apiKey: Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable("OPENAI_API_KEY")!
);

// Step 2: Wrap in Microsoft.Extensions.AI.OpenAIChatClient
IChatClient chatClient = new Microsoft.Extensions.AI.OpenAIChatClient(openAIClient);
```

### Class: OpenAIChatClient
Implements `IChatClient` by wrapping OpenAI's ChatClient.

```csharp
public class OpenAIChatClient : IChatClient, IDisposable
{
    public OpenAIChatClient(OpenAI.Chat.ChatClient client)

    public Task<ChatMessage> GetResponseAsync(
        IEnumerable<ChatMessage> messages,
        ChatOptions? options = null,
        CancellationToken cancellationToken = default
    )

    public IAsyncEnumerable<StreamingChatCompletionUpdate> GetStreamingResponseAsync(
        IEnumerable<ChatMessage> messages,
        ChatOptions? options = null,
        CancellationToken cancellationToken = default
    )
}
```

### Interface: IChatClient
Core chat client interface.

**KEY METHODS:**
```csharp
public interface IChatClient
{
    Task<ChatMessage> GetResponseAsync(
        IEnumerable<ChatMessage> messages,
        ChatOptions? options = null,
        CancellationToken cancellationToken = default
    );

    IAsyncEnumerable<StreamingChatCompletionUpdate> GetStreamingResponseAsync(
        IEnumerable<ChatMessage> messages,
        ChatOptions? options = null,
        CancellationToken cancellationToken = default
    );

    object? GetService(Type serviceType, object? key = null);
    TService? GetService<TService>(object? key = null) where TService : class;
}
```

