## AGENT CREATION

### Constructor Signature
```csharp
public ChatClientAgent(
    IChatClient chatClient,
    ChatClientAgentOptions options,
    ILoggerFactory? loggerFactory = null,
    IServiceProvider? serviceProvider = null
)
```

### Options Class
```csharp
var options = new ChatClientAgentOptions
{
    Id = "agent-id",
    Name = "Agent Name",
    Description = "What this agent does",
    Instructions = "System prompt / instructions",
    Tools = new List<AITool> { /* tools */ },

    // Optional:
    ChatHistoryProvider = null,           // Custom history storage
    ContextProviders = null,              // AI context enrichers
    MessageContextProviders = null,       // Message enrichers
    PersistChatHistory = false,           // Auto-save history
    ConversationIdPrefix = "prefix-"      // For multi-tenant
};

var agent = new ChatClientAgent(chatClient, options);
```

---

## CREATING IChatClient FROM OPENAI

```csharp
using OpenAI.Chat;
using Microsoft.Extensions.AI;

// Create OpenAI ChatClient
var openAIClient = new ChatClient(
    model: "gpt-4o-mini",
    apiKey: Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable("OPENAI_API_KEY")!
);

// Wrap in Microsoft's IChatClient
IChatClient chatClient = new Microsoft.Extensions.AI.OpenAIChatClient(openAIClient);
```

### IChatClient Interface
```csharp
public interface IChatClient
{
    Task<ChatMessage> GetResponseAsync(
        IEnumerable<ChatMessage> messages,
        ChatOptions? options = null,
        CancellationToken cancellationToken = default);

    IAsyncEnumerable<StreamingChatCompletionUpdate> GetStreamingResponseAsync(
        IEnumerable<ChatMessage> messages,
        ChatOptions? options = null,
        CancellationToken cancellationToken = default);
}
```

---

## DEFINING TOOLS

### Simple Delegate Tool
```csharp
var tools = new List<AITool>
{
    new AITool
    {
        Function = AIFunctionFactory.Create(
            (string query) => $"Results for: {query}",
            name: "SearchWeb",
            description: "Search the web for information"
        )
    },
    new AITool
    {
        Function = AIFunctionFactory.Create(
            (string url) => FetchContent(url),
            name: "FetchURL",
            description: "Fetch content from a URL"
        )
    }
};
```

### Method-based Tool
```csharp
public class Tools
{
    public string SearchWeb(string query) 
        => $"Found results for {query}";
}

var toolsInstance = new Tools();

var tool = new AITool
{
    Function = AIFunctionFactory.Create(
        method: typeof(Tools).GetMethod(nameof(Tools.SearchWeb))!,
        instance: toolsInstance,
        name: "SearchWeb",
        description: "Search the web"
    )
};
```

### AIFunctionFactory Methods
```csharp
// From delegate
AIFunctionFactory.Create(
    (string arg) => ProcessArg(arg),
    "FunctionName",
    "Function description"
);

// From method with instance
AIFunctionFactory.Create(
    method: typeof(MyClass).GetMethod("MyMethod")!,
    instance: myInstance,
    name: "MyTool",
    description: "What it does"
);

// With options
AIFunctionFactory.Create(
    (string arg) => DoSomething(arg),
    options: new AIFunctionFactoryOptions { /* config */ }
);
```

---

## RUNNING/INVOKING AGENT

### All RunAsync Variants
```csharp
// String input
var response = await agent.RunAsync(
    input: "Hello agent",
    session: session,
    options: runOptions,
    cancellationToken: default
);

// ChatMessage input
var response = await agent.RunAsync(
    message: new ChatMessage(ChatRole.User, "Hello"),
    session: session,
    options: runOptions
);

// Multiple messages
var response = await agent.RunAsync(
    messages: new[] {
        new ChatMessage(ChatRole.System, "You are helpful"),
        new ChatMessage(ChatRole.User, "Please help")
    },
    session: session,
    options: runOptions
);

// Empty (continue conversation)
var response = await agent.RunAsync(
    session: session,
    options: runOptions
);

// Generic typed output
var typedResponse = await agent.RunAsync<MyResultType>(
    session: session,
    options: runOptions
);
MyResultType result = typedResponse.Output;
```

### Streaming Variants
```csharp
await foreach (var update in agent.RunStreamingAsync(
    input: "Explain AI",
    session: session,
    options: runOptions
))
{
    if (update.Message != null)
    {
        Console.WriteLine($"Message: {update.Message.Text}");
    }

    if (update.FunctionCall != null)
    {
        Console.WriteLine($"Calling: {update.FunctionCall.FunctionName}");
    }

    if (update.FunctionResult != null)
    {
        Console.WriteLine($"Result: {update.FunctionResult.Result}");
    }
}
```

---

## CONFIGURING RUN OPTIONS

### ChatClientAgentRunOptions
```csharp
var runOptions = new ChatClientAgentRunOptions
{
    // Chat options
    ChatOptions = new ChatOptions
    {
        Temperature = 0.7,              // Randomness (0-2)
        MaxOutputTokens = 2000,         // Max output
        TopP = 0.9,                     // Nucleus sampling
        TopK = 40,                      // Top-K sampling
        Instructions = "Extra prompt",
        Tools = tools,                  // Available tools
        ConversationId = "conv-123",    // For tracking
        ToolCallBehavior = ToolCallBehavior.EnabledForAll
    },

    // Agent options (inherited from AgentRunOptions)
    MaximumIterations = 10,             // Max loop turns
    TimeLimit = TimeSpan.FromMinutes(5) // Max time
};
```

### ChatOptions Properties
- `Temperature` - 0 to 2 (default 1.0), higher = more random
- `MaxOutputTokens` - Max tokens in response
- `TopP` - Nucleus sampling (0-1)
- `TopK` - Top K tokens
- `Instructions` - Per-request system prompt
- `Tools` - Tools available for this request
- `ConversationId` - For conversation tracking
- `ToolCallBehavior` - EnabledForAll, DisabledForAll, etc.

---

## SESSIONS & CONVERSATION HISTORY

### Creating Sessions
```csharp
// New session
var session = await agent.CreateSessionAsync();

// Session with custom ID
var session = await agent.CreateSessionAsync(
    conversationId: "custom-conversation-id"
);

// Access session data
string id = session.Id;
IEnumerable<ChatMessage> history = session.History;
Dictionary<string, object?> state = session.State;
```

### Serializing Sessions
```csharp
// Save session to string (DB/file)
string serialized = await session.SerializeAsync();

// Restore session
var restoredSession = await AgentSession.DeserializeAsync(serialized);
```

---

## CHAT MESSAGES

### Creating Messages
